      <hedline>
        <hl1>IONA SPEECH LAB RECEIVES GRANT</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Elsa Brenner</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Brenner, Elsa</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Marjorie C Adams Charitable Trust grants $10,000 to Iona College speech language pathology department to enable it to become center for detecting hearing loss in infants and toddlers (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>The speech language pathology department at Iona College has received a $10,000 grant that will enable it to become a center for detecting hearing loss in infants and toddlers. The grant, from the Marjorie C. Adams Charitable Trust, will provide Iona with equipment so it can teach up to 70 students how to test infants for hearing losses. The college offers a bachelor's degree in speech-language pathology and audiology.</p>
        <p>Elsa Brenner</p>
      </block>
